memberdef.name: move

detaileddescription.para:
Move the object to the position of another SpatialObject with a specified duration. It use the acceleration, deceleration and the maximum speed of the MovableSpatialObject. If the acceleration is <= 0 OR deceleration of the object is >= 0, then the kinematical attributes won't be calculated and the movement will start with the speed needed to arrive the destination in time. If the maximum speed of the object is initialized (>0), then an IllegalMoveException will be thrown if it is not possible to make to the destination in time. If the object is already moving it will move to the new destination. (not for MovableSpatialSimProcess)
destination
The destination object we want to move to.
enttryPointName
The name of the specific entry point at the destination object, which should be steered to.
duration
The duration of the movement in TimeSpan.
focusOnTrack
Whether the orientation of the moving object should focus to the moving direction.

memberdef.argsstring: (SpatialObject destination, String entryPointName, TimeSpan duration, double maxSpeed, double acc, double dec, boolean focusOnTrack)
memberdef.name: move

detaileddescription.para: Move the object to the position of another SpatialObject with specific attributes. There are different varieties of movement modes depends on the initialized parameters (O = initialized, X = not initialized(means invalid or null)):
case 1: duration O, maxSpeed O, acc & dec O: The movement will be performed according to the parameters. If the given parameters can't be satisfied, an IllegalMoveException will be thrown.
case 2: duration X, maxSpeed O, acc & dec O: The object will be moved to the destination with the fastest speed possible.

case 3: duration O, maxSpeed X, acc & dec O: The object will move to the destination with the given acceleration and deceleration and try to reach the destination in time. If the given parameters can't be satisfied, an IllegalMoveException will be thrown.
case 4: duration X, maxSpeed X, acc & dec O: The object will be accelerated and followed by a deceleration. There's no constant phase in the movement.

case 5: duration O, maxSpeed O, acc or dec X: The object will start with the speed needed to arrive the destination in the given time and break suddenly to zero at the end of the movement. The maxSpeed gives the speed limit of the movement. If the given parameters can't be satisfied, an IllegalMoveException will be thrown.
case 6: duration X, maxSpeed O, acc or dec X: The movement will start with the maxSpeed and stops the destination.
case 7: duration O, maxSpeed X, acc or dec X: The movement will start with the speed needed to arrive the destination with the duration given.
All other combinations of these parameters will cause an IllegalMoveException.

If the object is already moving it will move to the new destination. (not for MovableSpatialSimProcess)
destination
The destination object we want to move to.
enttryPointName
The name of the specific entry point at the destination object, which should be steered to.

maxSpeed
The maximum speed of the movement(optional).

The acceleration of the movement(optional).

The deceleration of the movement(optional).

The class represents the movable DESMO-J Entities which should be visualized. Therefore it implements the MovableSpatialObject interface for the handling with the 3D spatial data, the spatial movements and the parent-child-MSO concept.
